  "title": "Admin and Accounts Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Accounts Payable:</strong> Sort, code, and\n     match invoices, set invoices up for payment, enter and upload invoices into\n     Xero, track expenses, process expense reports, and prepare electronic\n     transfers and payments.</li><li><strong>General Ledger (G/L) Data Entries:</strong>\n     Generate G/L details for year end closing.</li><li><strong>Month-End Closing:</strong> Perform\n     month-end close procedures.</li><li><strong>Financial Reporting:</strong> Prepare and\n     maintain financial reports and records.</li><li><strong>Accounts Receivable:</strong> Issue\n     customers’ invoices from Xero.</li><li><strong>Prepare Monthly payroll and CPF Submission</strong></li><li><strong>Application for Work permit for employee</strong></li><li><strong>Application for Grant whenever needed</strong></li><li><strong>Collection of debts, when needed</strong></li><li><strong>Ad-Hoc Tasks:</strong> Perform various tasks\n     as required.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Diploma in Accounting or\n     equivalent.</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> 2 to 3 years of\n     experience in accounting or finance.</li><li><strong>Skills:</strong> Proficient in Microsoft\n     Office, especially Excel, and accounting software, Xero. Strong attention\n     to detail, organizational skills, and the ability to work independently.</li></ul>",
